    • NK_T4

      public static java.lang.String[] NK_T4​(java.lang.String dadName, java.lang.String momName, int dadYOB, int momYOB, int vintageYear)
      This is the implementation of the newly and carefully designed NK-T4 Algorithm of Universal Compatibility. It takes names of parents, year of birth of parents, and an optional vintage year as input. It returns a String array that contains recommended boy and girl names.
      Parameters:
      dadName - Name of dad
      momName - Name of mom
      dadYOB - Year of birth of dad
      momYOB - Year of birth of mom
      vintageYear - Optional vintage year input
      Returns:
      Array of String containing one boy name and one girl name

    • NK_T5

      public static java.lang.String NK_T5​(java.lang.String iName, java.lang.String iGender, int iYOB, java.lang.String iGenderMate, java.lang.String iPreference)
      This is the implementation of the newly and carefully designed NK-T5 Algorithm. It takes user's name, year of birth, gender, preference and soulmate's gender as input. It returns the soulmate's name.

    • NK_T6

      public static int NK_T6​(java.lang.String iName, java.lang.String iGender, int iYOB, java.lang.String iNameMate, java.lang.String iGenderMate, java.lang.String iPreference)
      This is the implementation of the newly and carefully designed NK-T6 Algorithm of Universal Compatibility. It takes user's name, year of birth, gender and soulmate's name and gender, and user's age preference as input. The algorithm then considers the frequency and ranking of the names to calculate a score. It returns a score of compatibility of the user and his/her soulmate.
      Parameters:
      iName - User's Name
      iGender - User's Gender
      iYOB - User's Year of Birth
      iNameMate - Soulmate's Name
      iGenderMate - Soulmate's Gender
      iPreference - User's Age Preference
      Returns:

    • returnYear

      public static int returnYear​(java.lang.String yob)
      This is a helper function to parse String inputs for year of birth. It returns the corresponding year in Integer type. It returns 0 for out of range integers. It returns -1 for invalid non-numerical inputs. It returns -2 for empty inputs.
      Parameters:
      yob - String extracted from text fields
      Returns:
      Corresponding year in Integer type, or error integers for incorrect inputs

    • returnNumber
